==English==
===Etymology===
From Middle English, from Old French ''[[elissir]]'', from Medieval Latin ''elixir'', from Arabic ''al-'iksīr'', probably from Greek ''xērion'', from ''xēros'', dry.

===Noun===
'''elixir''' (''plural'' '''elixirs''')

#A medicine or substance believed to have magical properties.

